cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.AI. 

This paper deals with the problem of dense video captioning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel framework that involves joint training and optimization, which falls under the scope of machine learning. Hence, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper uses the ActivityNet Captions dataset, which is related to multimedia analysis, making cs.MM (Multimedia) another possible sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the use of attribute-augmented video captioning architecture, which is a form of semantic understanding, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a possible sub-category as well.
